## Palette Types

### Categorical Palettes

For discrete data with distinct categories:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
view_cpal_palettes(c("main", "main_3", "main_4", "main_5", "main_6", "binary", "status"))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Categorical palettes for discrete data](colors-palettes_files/figure-html/categorical-palettes-1.png){width=80%}
:::
:::


**Usage example:**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x = factor(cyl), fill = factor(cyl))) +
  geom_bar() +
  scale_fill_cpal("main_3") +
  labs(title = "Count by Cylinder", x = "Cylinders", y = "Count") +
  theme_cpal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Using categorical palette](colors-palettes_files/figure-html/categorical-example-1.png){width=80%}
:::
:::


---

### Sequential Palettes

For continuous or ordered data:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
view_cpal_palettes(c("midnight_seq_4", "midnight_seq_5", "midnight_seq_6", "midnight_seq_8"))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Sequential palettes for continuous data](colors-palettes_files/figure-html/sequential-palettes-1.png){width=80%}
:::
:::


**Usage example:**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg, color = hp)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  scale_color_cpal_c("midnight_seq_5") +
  labs(
    title = "Fuel Efficiency by Weight",
    subtitle = "Color shows horsepower",
    x = "Weight (1000 lbs)",
    y = "Miles per Gallon",
    color = "Horsepower"
  ) +
  theme_cpal()
```

